Types of Restore modes :
	--Restore With no recovery -
		If we have multiple DBs backups then we have to use this Restore With no recovery.
		it is not accessable to the other users when ever we using Restore With no recovery, it means it is under restoring.
	--Restore With recovery - 
		DB will be online and it will be accessable to the user, it will be use full when ever we are having single DB backup.
	--Restore Stand by - 
		It is almost Restore With no recovery but users are able to read the data but unable to modify the data.
